  <subsubsection><title>Key Ideas</title></subsubsection>

<definition xml:id="def_spring-potential-energy">
	<title>Spring Potential Energy</title>
	<statement>
		<p></p>
	<p>The potential energy for an ideal spring is <me>U_{spring} = \frac{1}{2}kx^2</me> where <m>x</m> is the 
		displacement of the spring from its equilibrium position. </p>
	</statement>
	</definition>
	


	<subsubsection>
	<title>Activities</title>
			<investigation>
<title>Spring Compression</title>
<p></p>
			  <p>Is the following statement true or false: <q>If you compress or extend the same spring by the same distance, 
				the potential energy stored in the spring is the same.</q>  Explain your reasoning.</p>
			</investigation>
			<exploration>
<title>Mattress Springs</title>
<statement>
	<p></p>
			  <p>Many mattresses can be approximated as ideal springs.  
			  Estimate the potential energy stored in a mattress with <m>k = 24,000 \mathrm{~N/m}</m> 
			  when one person lies down on the mattress and compresses it by <m>2 \mathrm{~cm}</m>.</p>
</statement>
</exploration>
